ning%20debut%20season%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERohit%20has%20also%20won%20two%20Champions%20League%20T20%20titles%20with%20MI%20in%202011%20and%202013%2C%20the%20latter%20as%20a%20captain.%20The%20'Hitman'%20is%20MI's%20all-time%20highest%20run-getter%2C%20scoring%205%2C357%20runs%20in%20208%20matches%20and%20204%20innings%20at%20an%20average%20of%2029.59%20and%20a%20strike%20rate%20of%20almost%20130%2C%20with%20a%20century%20and%2035%20fifties%20in%20204%20innings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20youngster%2C%20Rohit%20also%20represented%20the%20now-defunct%20Deccan%20Chargers%2C%20a%20former%20Hyderabad%20franchise%20from%202008-2010.%20He%20played%2045%20matches%20for%20the%20team%2C%20scoring%201%2C170%20runs%20at%20an%20average%20of%2030.79%20and%20a%20strike%20rate%20of%20over%20131%2C%20with%20eight%20fifties%20in%2044%20innings.%20His%20best%20score%20was%2076*.%20He%20won%20the%20IPL%202009%20season%20with%20this%20franchise%2C%20making%20him%20a%20six-time%20IPL%20champion.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20veteran%20batter%20is%20the%20fourth-highest%20run-getter%20in%20IPL%20history%2C%20scoring%206%2C254%20runs%20in%20244%20matches%20at%20an%20average%20of%2029.63%20and%20a%20strike%20rate%20of%20130.15.%20He%20scored%20a%20century%20and%2042%20fifties%20in%20239%20innings%2C%20with%20the%20best%20score%20of%20109*.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20someone%20who%20has%20led%20MI%20for%20so%20long%2C%20Rohit%20is%20an%20institution%20in%20himself%2C%20with%20him%20and%20MI%20shaping%20the%20career%20trajectories%20of%20many%20future%20Indian%20stars%20like%20Ishan%20Kishan%2C%20Jasprit%20Bumrah%2C%20Yuzvendra%20Chahal%2C%20Hardik%20Pandya%2C%20Tilak%20Varma%2C%20Ambati%20Rayadu%2C%20etc.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESunrisers%20Hyderabad%20Squad%3A%20Mayank%20Agarwal%2C%20Abhishek%20Sharma%2C%20Rahul%20Tripathi%2C%20Aiden%20Markram%2C%20Heinrich%20Klaasen(w)%2C%20Abdul%20Samad%2C%20Shahbaz%20Ahmed%2C%20Marco%20Jansen%2C%20Pat%20Cummins(c)%2C%20Bhuvneshwar%20Kumar%2C%20Mayan