o-friendly.%20We%20used%20eco-bricks%20made%20of%20limestone%20and%20red%20clay%20for%20the%20walls%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EListing%20all%20the%20natural%20materials%20that%20he%20used%2C%20Rajchandar%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CBesides%20eco-bricks%2C%20we%20also%20used%20Athangudi%20Tiles.%20These%20tiles%20are%20made%20up%20of%20sand%20found%20near%20Athangudi%20River%20which%20is%20much%20more%20sustainable%20than%20normal%20tiles.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20ceiling%2C%20the%20scientist%20used%20a%20technique%20called%20filler%20slab%20technique%20to%20minimise%20the%20use%20of%20concrete.%20According%20to%20Studio%20DCode%2C%20%E2%80%9CFiller%20slab%20is%20an%20alternate%20slab%20construction%20technology%20where%20part%20of%20concrete%20in%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20slab%20is%20replaced%20by%20filler%20material.%E2%80%9D%20The%20roofs%20also%20have%20clay%20tiles%20on%20the%20roofs%20too.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20used%20red%20soil%2C%20lime%2C%20cow%20dung%2C%20rice%20dusk%2C%20egg%20and%20jaggery%20to%20make%20a%20paste%20for%20construction%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAdditionally%2C%20the%20homestay%20features%20rainwater%20harvesting%2C%20and%20they%20are%20in%20the%20process%20of%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F107005%2Fever-wondered-what-a-homemaker-thinks-of-solar-panels%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einstalling%20solar%20panels%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20harness%20the%20sun.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20also%20make%20compost%20out%20of%20our%20kitchen%20waste%2C%20which%20is%20then%20used%20in%20our%20garden.%20We%20grow%20all%20our%20plants%20and%20food%20organically%20so%20our%20guests%20can%20enjoy%20fresh%20food%20daily.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20place%20boasts%205%20bedrooms%2C%203%20balconies%2C%20and%203%20living%20spaces%20for%20guests%20to%20enjoy.%20%E2%80%9CWhile%20the%20homestay%20is%20shared%20by%20us