F03%2FTurmeric-1-1711519971.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-1-1711519971-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-1-1711519971-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-1-1711519971-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-1-1711519971-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-345838%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EAlongside%20cultivating%20vegetables%2C%20wheat%2C%20and%20maize%2C%20Kanchan%20sowed%20turmeric%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%202020.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EOld%20field%2C%20new%20crop%2C%20huge%20success%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EComing%20from%20an%20agricultural%20background%2C%20Kanchan%20turned%20to%20farming%20soon%20after%20her%20marriage.%20Alongside%20cultivating%20vegetables%2C%20wheat%2C%20and%20maize%2C%20the%20BA%20graduate%20sowed%20turmeric%20for%20the%20first%20time%20in%202020.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9COnce%2C%20I%20saw%20a%20programme%20on%20television%20that%20showcased%20the%20advantages%20of%20taking%20up%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F274975%2Fdivine-foods-helps-organic-turmeric-farmers-earn-double-sell-to-us-uk%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eturmeric%20farming%3C%2Fa%3E.%20To%20learn%20more%20about%20it%2C%20I%20went%20to%20the%20nearby%20KVK%20(Krishi%20Vigyan%20Kendra)%20and%20undertook%20a%20training%20programme%20of%20seven%20days%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKanchan%20opted%20for%20the%20Sangli%20variety%20of%20turmeric%20which%20has%20high%20curcumin%20turmeric%20and%20is%20often%20used%20for%20medicinal%20purposes.%20In%20addition%20to%20its%20deep-orange%20colour%20and%20rich%20aroma%2C%20Kanchan%20says%2C%20this%20variety%20produces%20big%20roots%20compared%20to%20other%20indigenous%20varieties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EShe%20procured%20eight%20quintals%20of%20%3Cem%3Ekachhi%20haldi%20%3C%2Fem%3E(seed)%20from%20KVK%20at%20Rs%2040%20per%20kg.%20%E2%80%9CThereafter%2C%20we%20started%20tilling%20the%20farmland%20to%20remove%20weeds%20and%20reduce%20the%20soil%20compaction%20%5Brelieve%20the%20tightness%20of%20soil%5D%2C%20and%20level%20the%20soil.%20After%20seedbed%20preparation%2C%20we%20added%20four%20trolleys%20(1%20trolley%20comprises%2040%20quintals)%20of%20cow%20dung%20in%20the%20soil.%20We%20then%20sowed%20germinated%20%3Cem%3Ekachhi%20haldi%20%3C%2Fem%3Ein%20the%20beds.%20The%20process%20is%20similar%20to%20sowing%20any%20tuber%20crop%20like%20potatoes%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-3-1711520093.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Kanchan%20claims%20she%20is%20the%20first%20such%20farmer%20to%20practice%20turmeric%20farming%20in%20this%20region.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-3-1711520093.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-3-1711520093-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-3-1711520093-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-3-1711520093-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-3-1711520093-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-345840%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EKanchan%20claims%20she%20is%20the%20first%20such%20farmer%20to%20practice%20turmeric%20farming%20in%20this%20region.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20turmeric%20farming%2C%20the%20soil%20is%20usually%20mounded%20around%20the%20base%20of%20a%20plant%20to%20get%20large%20rhizomes.%20At%20first%2C%20Kanchan%20says%20she%20did%20not%20know%20the%20right%20time%20to%20earth%20up%20the%20plant.%20She%20later%20learned%20that%20it%20was%20done%20a%20month%20after%20planting%20the%20crop.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20sowing%20period%20is%20between%20June%20and%20July%2C%20the%20crop%20is%20ready%20for%20harvest%20by%20February-end.%20She%20points%20out%20that%20it%20is%20very%20important%20to%20keep%20in%20mind%20the%20kind%20of%20soil%20used%20for%20cultivation.%20%E2%80%9COur%20region%20is%20famous%20for%20black%20soil%20that%20is%20suitable%20for%20wheat%20cultivation.%20However%2C%20a%20well-drained%20sandy%20loam%20soil%20rich%20in%20humus%20content%20works%20well%20for%20growing%20turmeric%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20informs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAlso%2C%20black%20soil%20is%20soft%20when%20wet%20but%20forms%20hard%20blocks%20when%20it%20gets%20dry.%20So%2C%20we%20need%20a%20sandy%20loamy%20solid%20that%20is%20well-drained.%20In%20our%20district%2C%20only%20a%20few%20blocks%20including%20our%20Kesla%20block%20have%20such%20soil%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETalking%20about%20the%20fertilisers%20and%20pesticides%20required%20for%20boosting%20turmeric%20growth%2C%20she%20says%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20only%20use%20cow%20dung%20and%20%3Cem%3Ejeevamrut%20%3C%2Fem%3E(liquid%20organic%20manure)%20to%20boost%20the%20fertility%20of%20the%20soil.%20Besides%2C%20as%20turmeric%20in%20itself%20is%20antiseptic%20and%20herbal%2C%20there%20are%20fewer%20chances%20of%20pest%20attack.%20Even%20if%20pests%20attack%20the%20crop%2C%20we%20use%20Trichoderma%20biopesticides%20to%20control%20the%20attack%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20she%20wanted%20to%20be%20careful%20of%20growing%20a%20new%20crop%2C%20Kanchan%20sowed%20and%20used%20only%20an%20acre%20of%20land%20to%20sow%20eight%20quintals%20of%20turmeric%20root.%20After%20eight%20months%2C%20she%20harvested%20bumper%20produce%20of%20100%20quintals.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-2-1711520044.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Last%20year%2C%20Kanchan%20got%20a%20bountiful%20harvest%20of%20400%20quintals%2C%20earning%20an%20income%20of%20Rs%2012%20lakh.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-2-1711520044.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-2-1711520044-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-2-1711520044-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-2-1711520044-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-2-1711520044-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-345839%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ELast%20year%2C%20Kanchan%20got%20a%20bountiful%20harvest%20of%20400%20quintals%2C%20earning%20an%20income%20of%20Rs%2012%20lakh.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EProcessing%20raw%20turmeric%20for%20good%20returns%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20harvesting%20the%20rhizomes%2C%20Kanchan%20processes%20the%20entire%20produce%20to%20sell%20it%20in%20powdered%20form.%20%E2%80%9COnce%20we%20wash%20the%20roots%2C%20we%20boil%20them%20in%20water%20and%20dry%20them%20completely%20under%20the%20sunlight.%20Thereafter%2C%20we%20peel%20the%20roots%20and%20grind%20them.%20It%20takes%20about%2015%20days%20to%20process%20the%20%3Cem%3Ekachhi%20haldi%3C%2Fem%3E%20(raw%20turmeric)%20into%20powder%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20a%20batch%20of%20100%20quintals%2C%20only%2020%20quintals%20are%20left%20after%20processing.%20But%20this%20step%20is%20extremely%20advantageous%20as%20powder%20turmeric%20gets%20higher%20returns%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20Kanchan%20earned%20Rs%203%20lakh%20against%20the%20input%20costs%20of%20Rs%2050%2C000.%20Currently%2C%20she%20has%20expanded%20turmeric%20cultivation%20on%2010%20acres%20of%20land.%20%E2%80%9CThis%20season%2C%20we%20expect%20an%20income%20of%20Rs%2030%20lakh%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%20with%20pride.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterestingly%2C%20Kanchan%20makes%201%20kg%20packets%20of%20powdered%20turmeric%20and%20sells%20entire%20produce%20on%20the%20farm%20itself.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20do%20not%20need%20to%20go%20to%20the%20local%20market%20as%20we%20have%20earned%20great%20demand%20at%20the%20local%20level.%20By%20the%20time%20any%20outside%20customer%20reaches%20us%2C%20we%20have%20usually%20sold%20all%20our%20produce.%20Also%2C%20we%20sell%20our%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F260973%2Frajasthan-couple-turmeric-revolution-earns-lakhs-suicides-organic-farming%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eorganic%20turmeric%20%3C%2Fa%3Eat%20Rs%20150%20per%20kg%20compared%20to%20Rs%20240%20per%20kg%20in%20the%20local%20market.%20We%20do%20not%20have%20any%20issue%20lowering%20the%20price%20as%20our%20cost%20of%20production%20becomes%20less%20with%20organic%20methods%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKanchan%20claims%20she%20is%20the%20first%20such%20farmer%20to%20practice%20turmeric%20farming%20in%20this%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLocal%20farmers%20here%20were%20reluctant%20to%20grow%20turmeric%20as%20it%20has%20a%20longer%20growing%20season%20but%20they%20ignored%20the%20fact%20that%20it%20gives%20definitive%20and%20huge%20returns.%20Other%20than%20being%20able%20to%20earn%20double%20income%2C%20it%20gives%20me%20immense%20contentment%20that%20I%20grow%20the%20produce%20organically.%20The%20more%20we%20minimise%20the%20use%20of%20chemical%20pesticides%2C%20the%20more%20toxin-free%20food%20will%20be%20there%20for%20our%20kids%20to%20eat%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20shares.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Pranita%20Bhat.%20All%20photos%3A%20Kanchan%20Verma.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711523112000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F03%2FTurmeric-1-1711519971.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D345836%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Farmers%20traditionally%20cultivate%20wheat%20in%20Narmadapuram%2C%20Madhya%20Pradesh.%20But%20Kanchan%20Verma's%20decision%20to%20transition%20to%20turmeric%20farming%20resulted%20in%20increased%20income.%20She%20uses%20organic%20methods%20and%20also%20sells%20powdered%20turmeric%20for%20higher%20returns.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F345836%2Fmadhya-pradesh-farmer-kanchan-verma-earns-double-income-growing-organic-turmeric%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22'Taliban%20vows%20to%20publicly%20stone%20women%20to%20death%20for%20adultery'%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1711522732000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-108812167%2Cimgsize-1027095.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fsouth-asia%2Ftaliban-vows-to-publicly-stone-women-to-death-for-adultery%2Farticleshow%2F108811767.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Taliban's%20supreme%20leader%2C%20Mullah%20Hibatullah%20Akhundzada%2C%20reaffirmed%20the%20group's%20commitment%20to%20harsh%20policies%20towards%20women%2C%20including